"anchor":"discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Use this modifier on a ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Toggle","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" instance to set a style that defines","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the control’s appearance and behavior. For example, you can choose","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/ToggleStyle\/switch","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" style:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["Toggle(\"Vibrate on Ring\", isOn: $vibrateOnRing)","    .toggleStyle(.switch)"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Built-in styles typically have a similar appearance across platforms,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"tailored to the platform’s overall style:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"table","header":"row","rows":[[[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Platform","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Appearance"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"iOS, iPadOS","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"macOS","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[],"type":"paragraph"}]]]},{"type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Styling toggles in a hierarchy","anchor":"Styling-toggles-in-a-hierarchy"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"You can set a style for all toggle instances within a view hierarchy","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"by applying the style modifier to a container view. For example, you","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"can apply the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ToggleStyle\/button"},{"text":" style to an ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/HStack","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":":","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["HStack {","    Toggle(isOn: $isFlagged) {","        Label(\"Flag\", systemImage: \"flag.fill\")","    }","    Toggle(isOn: $isMuted) {","        Label(\"Mute\", systemImage: \"speaker.slash.fill\")","    }","}",".toggleStyle(.button)"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The example above has the following appearance when ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"isFlagged"},{"text":" is","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"true"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"isMuted"},{"text":" is ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"false"},{"text":":","type":"text"}]},{"type":"table","header":"row","rows":[[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Platform","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Appearance","type":"text"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"iOS, iPadOS","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"macOS"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[]}]]]},{"type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Automatic styling","anchor":"Automatic-styling"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If you don’t set a style, OpenSwiftUI assumes a value of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ToggleStyle\/automatic"},{"type":"text","text":", which corresponds to a context-specific"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"default. Specify the automatic style explicitly to override a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"container’s style and revert to the default:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["HStack {","    Toggle(isOn: $isShuffling) {","        Label(\"Shuffle\", systemImage: \"shuffle\")","    }","    Toggle(isOn: $isRepeating) {","        Label(\"Repeat\", systemImage: \"repeat\")","    }","","    Divider()","","    Toggle(\"Enhance Sound\", isOn: $isEnhanced)","        .toggleStyle(.automatic) \/\/ Revert to the default style.","}",".toggleStyle(.button) \/\/ Use button style for toggles in the stack.",".labelStyle(.iconOnly) \/\/ Omit the title from any labels."]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The style that OpenSwiftUI uses as the default depends on both the platform","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"and the context. In macOS, the default in most contexts is a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"ToggleStyle\/checkbox","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", while in iOS, the default toggle style is a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/ToggleStyle\/switch","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":":","type":"text"}]},{"type":"table","header":"row","rows":[[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Platform","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Appearance"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"iOS, iPadOS"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"macOS"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[]}]]]},{"type":"aside","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Like toggle style does for toggles, the ","type":"text"},{"code":"View\/labelStyle(_:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"modifier sets the style for ","type":"text"},{"code":"Label","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" instances in the hierarchy. The","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"example above demostrates the compact ","type":"text"},{"code":"LabelStyle\/iconOnly","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" style,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"which is useful for button toggles in space-constrained contexts.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Always include a descriptive title for better accessibility.","type":"text"}]}],"name":"Note","style":"note"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"For more information about how OpenSwiftUI chooses a default toggle style,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"see the ","type":"text"},{"code":"ToggleStyle\/automatic","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" style.","type":"text"}]}],"kind":"content"}],"kind":"symbol","references":{"doc://OpenSwiftUI/documentation/OpenSwiftUI/HStack":{"type":"topic","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"HStack","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"HStack","url":"\/documentation\/openswiftui\/hstack","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/HStack","abstract":[{"text":"A view that arranges its subviews in a horizontal line.","type":"text"}],"role":"symbol","kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"HStack","kind":"identifier"}]},"doc://OpenSwiftUI/documentation/OpenSwiftUI/View":{"fragments":[{"text":"protocol","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"View","kind":"identifier"}],"kind":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"View","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"View","type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A type that represents part of your app’s user interface and provides"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"modifiers that you use to configure views."}],"url":"\/documentation\/openswiftui\/view","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/View","role":"symbol"},"doc://OpenSwiftUI/documentation/OpenSwiftUI/ToggleStyle":{"kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"protocol","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"ToggleStyle","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"ToggleStyle","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/ToggleStyle","role":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The appearance and behavior of a toggle."}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"ToggleStyle","kind":"identifier"}],"type":"topic","url":"\/